content:
Darline Bertil is so amazing! 
She lost both hands in the 2010 earthquake in Haiti. She graduated from Hunter today and wants to help disabled kids. The last thing she wants is pity. 
Darline can put on her own lipstick, thank you, w her robotic hands!
Congrats Darline! You are fab!!

content:
This is Martha. She was just crowned World's Ugliest Dog at an ugly dog contest in Petaluma, CA. She's a Neopolitan Mastiff. She's 3 years old, 125 lbs w 300 lbs of skin. She drools, is clumsy and bossy. The judges and crowd loved her! Sweet Martha, who is being fostered by Shirley Dawn Zindler for the Dogwood Animal Rescue Group, takes home $1,500 and a monumental, 5-foot-tall trophy.  
Personally, I don't think any of God's creatures are ugly! 
Go Martha!

content:
While I was working hard at the beach in Florida, my little guy back in NY wiped out on his scooter. His legs and arms got quite cut up. He continued on to baseball practice, his coaches cleaned him up and he worked out w the team. He sent me photos after he came home. What a trooper.
My older one scraped his knee too today, while sliding into 3rd base. Are they twins? 
Scrapes and scars are signs of a fun summer!

Meanwhile, I made steak and eggs with a side of fruit for my big boy in Florida before his morning game. But my breakfast seems lame in comparison and not photo worthy.

content:
Today is my wedding anniversary! How many, you ask? 24 glorious years. My husband is in Amsterdam for work. I am in Florida w my older son. Our schedules are crazy and so is our love for each other.
So, we celebrate ❤️ everyday, in big ways and small, in acts of kindness and respect, in countless hugs and kisses, in forgiving each other, in holding hands, in trying to figure out how best to parent our dear children, in support of each other's dreams and struggles, in laughter, in prayer, in friendship, in love. 
Happy Anniversary, Husband! God bless you always!!
